  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community-based Child Protection  for the most  vulnerable populations in Nangarhar,  Laghman and Kunar Provinces &#x2013; Ijtema- 4</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since Dec. 2015, Tdh had been implementing several projects with CHF funding in Nangarhar, Kunar and Laghman provinces. Since the needs of the population remain high and since the approach of former projects proved to be effective, Tdh proposes to embark on a new project for highly affected IDPs, returnees, returned IDPs and conflict affected population of the provinces Nangarhar, Kunar and Laghman. The project intends to strengthen the resilience of these groups by reducing vulnerabilities through access to information on CP, by addressing specific needs through community delivered life-saving psycho-social services,  the establishment of a case management system (protection) and by strengthening protection mechanisms through Community Based Child Protection Committees (CBCPC) and volunteers. These activities will be delivered to in order to improve the coping mechanism of children and to detect most vulnerable children in need of further assistance.  The activities will be implemented by expert Tdh social worker and social animator in the mention district which mention below.  This 12-months project (from 1st May 2020 to 30th April 2021 will be implemented in the Eastern provinces as follows: 
- In Nangarhar: Mohmandara district (4 villages), Durbaba district (4 villages), Bati Kot district (4 villages), Chaparhar district (4 villages),- Kunar: Norgal district (4 villages) Khas Kunar district (4 villages), Laghman: Qarghayi district (4villages) and Mehtarlam district(4 villages). 
The data collected during the planned IJTEMA4 activities will be shared with the clusters and OCHA regularly and, when relevant, will be shared with other partners for further support for the intervention area. The sustainability and relevancy of the proposed project will be reinforced by integrating lessons learned and impact analysis based on the assessment report. Tdh will establish CFSs for the children who are at risk of violence in four provinces in the east region of the country focus most on the hard to reach district.</narrative>
  </description>
